    <text type="letter">
        <body>

            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Concord <choice>
                            <abbr>Mass:</abbr>
                            <expan>Massachusetts</expan>
                        </choice></name>
                    <date when="1881-09-19"><choice>
                            <abbr>Sept:</abbr>
                            <expan>September</expan>
                        </choice> 19 '81</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear John<!--<ptr target="n0129"/>--></salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I keep on fairly in health &amp; strength&#8212;have been out here a few days the
                guest of Mr &amp; Mrs F B Sanborn<!--<ptr target="n0538"/>-->&#8212;&amp; everything most affectionate &amp; hospitable from
                them both&#8212;&amp; from others&#8212;Have had a curiously full and satisfactory
                time with Emerson<!--<ptr target="n0218"/>-->&#8212;he came to see me Saturday evening early, Mrs E<!--<ptr target="n3064"/>--> also, &amp; <choice>
                    <orig>staid</orig>
                    <reg>stayed</reg>
                </choice> two hours&#8212;Yesterday I went there (by pressing invitation) to dinner,
                &amp; <choice>
                    <orig>staid</orig>
                    <reg>stayed</reg>
                </choice> two hours&#8212;a wonderfully good two hours&#8212;the whole family were
                very cordial, including Mrs. E. &amp; the son, Edward, a doctor, a fine, handsome,
                'cute, glowing young man, with a beautiful wife and child<!--<ptr target="n3064"/>-->&#8212;I took to them
                all&#8212;I cannot tell you how sweet and good (and all as it should be) Emerson <choice>
                    <orig>look'd</orig>
                    <reg>looked</reg>
                </choice> and behaved&#8212;he did not talk, in the way of joining in any animated
                conversation, but pleasantly and hesitatingly &amp; sparsely&#8212;fully
                enough&#8212;to me it seemed just as it should be&#8212;</p>

            <p>The book is about through&#8212;will appear last of October&#8212;every thing
                satisfactory&#8212;I go from here in about a week to Johnston's,<!--<ptr target="n0336"/>--> <choice>
                    <abbr>cor:</abbr>
                    <expan>correspondence</expan>
                </choice> Mott avenue &amp; 149th <choice>
                    <abbr>St.</abbr>
                    <expan>Street</expan>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <abbr>N.Y.</abbr><expan>New York</expan></choice>&#8212;then to Camden&#8212;shall go to Canada this winter&#8212;</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
